    <summary>Universal compiler and interpreter wrapper for 30+ programming languages</summary>
    <description>
Polyglot is a universal compiler and interpreter wrapper that detects programming languages by file extension and executes them with the appropriate toolchain.

## Features

- Supports 30+ programming languages
- Automatic language detection
- Auto-install missing toolchains
- Watch mode for development
- Colored output
- Comprehensive configuration
- Dry-run mode
- Progress indicators

## Supported Languages

Interpreted: Python, JavaScript, Ruby, PHP, Perl, Lua, Shell, Elixir, Erlang, Groovy, R, Julia, TypeScript, Dart

Compiled: Go, Java, C, C++, Rust, Zig, Nim, Crystal, D, Haskell, OCaml, F#, Kotlin, Scala, Swift

Esoteric: Brainfuck

## Usage

```
polyglot run hello.py
polyglot watch app.js
polyglot list
```
